<title>xStreamBufferBytesAvailable</title>
<indexterm><primary>xStreamBufferBytesAvailable</primary></indexterm>

<para><link linkend="_stream__buffer_8h">stream_buffer.h</link></para>

<para><literallayout>
size_t <link linkend="_stream__buffer_8h_1af32d1737de29f24ee31ac1e3c407d9fd">xStreamBufferBytesAvailable( StreamBufferHandle_t xStreamBuffer )</link>;
</literallayout></para>

<para>Queries a stream buffer to see how much data it contains, which is equal to the number of bytes that can be read from the stream buffer before the stream buffer would be empty.</para>

<para>
                <formalpara>
                    <title>
Parameters</title>
                    <para>
                    <table frame="all">
                        <tgroup cols="2" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
                        <colspec colwidth="4*"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
<entry>xStreamBuffer</entry><entry>
<para>The handle of the stream buffer being queried.</para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    </para>
                </formalpara>
                <formalpara><title>Returns</title>

<para>The number of bytes that can be read from the stream buffer before the stream buffer would be empty. </para>
</formalpara>
</para>
